{
  "texts": [
    "JHEP04(2024)048where dµ is an appropriate measure on the moduli space M g,n of n-punctured, genus g Riemann surfaces, Ψ is a generic label denoting all of the fields in the theory and S[Ψ] is the action (2.27) which includes the Fradkin-Tseytlin term for Φ.",
    "We will say more about dµ below but for now, we take it to include 3g -3 b-ghost insertions b(µ I) = Σ d 2 z G -(z)µ I (z) = Σ d 2 z b(z)µ I (z) +...,where the ellipsis denotes the compact part of G -, which we know from appendix B does not contribute to physical correlation functions.",
    "Moreover, {µ I } denote a basis of Beltrami differentials so thatdµ = n+3g-3 I=1 b(µ I)dτ I,where {τ I } are coordinates on M g,n.",
    "Assuming dµ is invariant under the transformation generated by K, the variation of the correlation function can be found using the commutatorδ K (•) = [αK, •], δ K C g (x, w) = -2α C 0 dz ∂Φ(z) n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i) + 2α(1 -g) n-2+2g α=1 W (u α) n i=1 V w i m i 1,m i 2 (x i; z i)where the second term comes from the variation of the Fradkin-Tseytlin term.",
    "The minus sign in front of the first term comes from viewing the contour C 0 to be around the complement of the disc around z = 0 in Σ g, rather than z = 0."
  ]
}